The paper deals with the problem of person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel visual word co-occurrence model, which involves unsupervised learning and linear SVMs, indicating a focus on machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also deals with image processing and feature extraction, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves searching and matching images, which could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to solve a challenging problem, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
